Would have loved to try it. The menu or website should mention that they are a cash only business. We drove quite a way only to see a fading sign on the door that turned us in the opposite direction because the line was pretty long and it was closer to closing time. Giving 3 stars because the menu sounded great.
Got two 50mg cookies and it was perfect for my friend I 11/10 thanks very much❤️❤️
Amazing lemonade!! The nut muffin was also delicious and I was definitely zooted! Will be back soon!
Great Customer experience but was super expensive....didn't  expect that at all when u arrive....still was happy  with purchasing
went today & got an edible for me and my sister & the cashier was awesome ! And the edibles were bomb 😜

I liked the vibe the space was VERY SMALL so in these times it was order and go which is understandable. The options were good of snacks and drinks. BUT pricing was shady, why is a small cup of lemonade before you get anything "special" in it $5? Is this Starbucks...I'd get more lemonade there for 5$. Then the prices for the delta 8 (THC they have) additions didnt reflect that it was just the reg price of items and there was separate THC price (so like lemonade 5$ plus the THC price) you could quickly end up spending $30+ on just a small drink. Which is understandable if the strengths matched the pricing. I'd rather bought a delta 8 cart than had these treats for the price they currently are. Also delta 8 "elevation " comes and goes quickly... I liked the place but there definitely needs to be several improvements and better organization before I'm willing to go back and drop a lot of money there again. Also its cash only so bring at LEAST $50 cash before you go...per person. I really would give this 2.5 stars but 3 for benefit of the doubt.

This place is what it's all about!!! The setup is so zen ,Guys there are very knowledgeable and attentive. The cheesecake was delicious ,The menu is extensive and offers an opportunity to try new things. Awesome experience!! If you're an enthusiast, make it a point to get here!! I came all the way from Atlanta to experience it!!😁😁
Service was amazing. Everyone I encountered from the entrance to checking out was friendly. Their variety and options are some of the best I've seen yet.

Disappointed. My boyfriend and I were standing in line for about 20 minutes. someone checked our IDs and denied my boyfriends because his was expired. He looks at mine and instantly tells me I cant use it because there was a small part of the corner missing. We both said ok and started walking away and this man was to rudely comment to us, "Yea sorry guys we're selling drugs here"...... We then went to a recreational dispensary; where they sell drugs, used both our IDs no problems.
Love the cozy environment and the staff is super friendly

I asked a few questions about sourcing, testing, etc and no one could answer my questions. The manager  who spoke with me said he could show me a COA then backtracked to say he wasn't allowed access to that info and needed a higher level manager, of which none were available.  This problem lies completely on management. The staff knew how to be baristas (only reason for 2 stars over 1),  but were completely under-trained in hemp, cannabis, Delta 8, CBD, etc. Coming from a restaurant and cannabis background, I can't recommend this shop.
Fricken awesome place. Staff is amazing and made me feel super welcome and very informative!
Great little hidden Gem in the city, Excellent Americano infused with THC. Great service & Great happy people here. Will be returning! Thank you Wake- N- Bake

This shop is not what it sounds to be.  When I went in, the crew was fantastic and they definitely weren’t scared to recommend the best for me. Unfortunately when I decided to order something with thc, it really didn’t do anything for me and the portions are pretty small as perusal in Chicago. I can say I’m an active thc user, and that it would be much better and cheaper making edibles at home. Although the shop’s items may taste better, you will FEEL much better making them at home. In order for Wake N Bake to thrive, I would love to see them keep the same products just make them stronger and maybe it would be more worth the price. The THC just was not there for the most part and it was very expensive. Most likely will not be coming back, maybe only for the coffee.
Staff is extremely knowledgeable and friendly! I love every drink and treat I've had so far and plan of being a regular.

This place is amazing and well run with knowledgeable staff. They definitely had me zooted with the strawberry cough with 60mg of delta 8! Drove 6 hrs just to go to this establishment and absolutely no regrets. As a cancer patient this trip was part of my bucket list and was not let down. We had so much fun.

Had an amazing lavender vanilla latte ! The staff seems like they they are genuinely passionate about thier job. Super knowledgeable individuals ! Definitely will be  coming back . Thank you guys soooo much for yall services !
Absolutely loved the red velvet cake

I can. I drug text at work on my label of my food was (see attached photo.) be more careful of your labling. I tried to email you guys and no one got back to me I emailed the company on the lid and they helped me but I also had to call your bakery cause I was that paranoid- to make sure I didn't consume THC. I purchased your Groupon. I had no idea thats the products that are sold. be more clear in your labeling that is something that is very important I could have lost my job if this was the case.  also the americano I ordered was alot to be desired and the almond milk was chunky.

I really wanna love this place more than I do, but unfortunately I have been disappointed both times I have gone.  Each time,  I spent roughly $60 for some edibles and two drinks for my partner and I - she is not a frequent user but I am - and both times we barely felt anything.  The bag of infused gummy worms didn't do anything, even though I ate nearly the whole thing myself. The coffee didn't do anything for me either. The only saving grace was the chocolate chip cookie we split that actually gave us a decent feeling! But for only 1 product out of the several that I paid for to work is disappointing.  I wanna keep giving this place my business because I love the idea, the vibe, and the staff, but I don't know if I can bring myself to drive 40 minutes, wait in line another 30-60mins, and spend $60+ for barely any effect.

Love, love, LOVE this place! As both a cannabis and coffee connoisseur I can say I am always satisfied. The staff is extremely friendly and helpful and its a variety of goodies to choose from. If you follow their Instagram they have a bunch of partner deals they do with local food businesses and also preview products that are or will be available in the stores. Highly recommend 😉
Cute place. Super friendly staff. The items I got were like regular candy. The baked good I got was extremely dry. I was excited but this place didn’t do it for me, waste of money imo.

Great experience, great coffee(recomend the pistachio latte) and the brownies and rice crispy were awesome. Thanks to the staff that was knowledgeable and made this an amazing experience! Btw follow the Manny's Mexican Minute page on FB to see the full video of our experience.
Amazing strawberry lemonade! Will definitely go back 😍
Awesome variety of products with something for everyone. Baked goods were delicious and made me feel great!

Probably one of the coolest coffee shops you could go to. They have great baked goods ;) An awesome coffee selection,  the pistachio latte is my absolute favorite, I like to add a little CBD or THC.  The staff is always really friendly and helpful. The shop has a cozy vibe to it with local art work hung around the room.

my latte was room temperature, not enjoyable at all. my partner and i didn’t feel anything and it was really expensive.... i was expecting way better tbh. i could have bought a great eighth with the money i spent lol smh

I rushed in to buy a snack not even having realized that they were closed. I for sure thought they closed at 7 but it clearly said 5 online so definitely my mistake. I told them I'd come back another day and they were so sweet to give me an option to get some sweets, even being $1.50+ short. I will definitely come back . That cinnamon scone was one of the best scones I've had, I have yet to try thhe lemon poppy seed but I'm sure it won't disappoint.

These people are amazing, worked with me on a super specific custom order that they EXCELLED on. 500mg into 6 lemon cupcakes and could barely taste anything except delicious lemon, shout out to y’all. Continue being great.
Can I order 2 infused drinks to go?
This place rocks. You're missing out if you haven't been there!
Wow,I love that place ,best edibles and infused treats in Chicago I can’t wait to go back
So damn delicious!

I ended up getting 2 infused drinks; 120mg for myself, a 30mg for my girl, both didn't hit, called the store, Johnny was very nice and offered to take care of me personally next time I go. Also got gummies that we took but didn't hit and Johnny also explained why they didn't hit. All in all, very professional and very helpful! Will visit again soon.

They decided that it was "too cold" and turned people away that had been waiting in line for 30+ mins. Then posted on their IG they were still open, baked goods only. Pretty disappointing for our first time.

It was generally a fun place to be at. The drinks and food are good. The service is amazing. It's a small little café. Since it's fairly small there was a line outside. So if you come here, expect that there will be a line. So come earlier than the closing time.
Amazing menu and staff to guide you through your choices. Cash only, but there's an ATM right outside if you need it. There can be a long line at times, but definitely worth the wait.

Honestly the iced vanilla lavender coffee was great. But this place is pretty mediocre. We bought two coffees and two burritos and it came out to $65. If the food was good, I wouldn't be complaining. But unfortunately when I bit into the sweet n heat burrito it had a piece of plastic. Also, it didn't taste fresh or too tasty. Definitely edible (apart from the plastic) LOL... When I called to let the manager know he mentioned that the food is bought from an outside source not made in kitchen. I understand, things happen. But that means that we spent over $40 on burritos that are premade.. Really all they did was add the THC in the salsa verde. Thank god for that because it definitely helped the experience. I'm all about spending money on good food but this was pretty disappointing. Also, the man who works there told me that I can do a pre order because I was on a time crunch.. I told him I would call back in 5 mins for my order. When I called back a lady answered and got kind of upset when I brought that up because I guess that's not something they do. I appreciate him working with us but there needs to be communication there. She put me on a brief hold after saying they can't do the pre order, and then the man that I spoke with got on the phone and sounded kind of upset that I was calling back (even though he told me it was okay) and took my order, then said in a upset tone "this is the last time we are doing this for you just so you know". I would've never called back with an order of pre ordering was an issue, he literally told me that was okay. I don't want to feel like i'm inconveniencing someone at all, I know how it is in the food industry. I just felt like more of a burden coming in. Once I got in, they were both extremely friendly and welcoming. VERY cute little spot. I might be back for the coffee. But to be honest after trying the food I was pretty disappointed. Hopefully they start making food in their kitchen that's fresh when the pandemic is over! Kudos to you guys for the great idea and sweet spot! Wish you the best.
Really nice staff, nice ambiance. Great drinks. A little line but well worth it. Definitely should try this place

Omg! Went here last Friday and this place exceeded my expectations....staff was super friendly, prices were fair (I got 30mg cafe con leche with 40mg cinnamon muffin, $30 total), and it started off my day perfect....lasted a long time for me!  Everything was delicious and the place was a total vibe! I had two people go since and they loved it as well.  I definitely will be returning regularly...this could be the new Starbucks ☺️

Once more, Wake-N-Bakery has NOT disappointed! I order a Double Dream Mocha with a dosage of 30 mg. The beverage was made with craft and care by a very kind barista (wish I got his name). The service was quick as I went before the work rush (be sure to get there maybe midday to avoid longer wait times as their popularity booms!) I also purchased a chocolate chip cookie that was dosed at 50 mg, the cookie was fresh and soft, but most certainly packed with a punch! About 1 hour into my delightful treats I started to feel full body relaxation and of course, some giggles! This is definitely the spot if you want to "treat yo-self!"

The staff was very nice! The place is nice and small! But unfortunately I bought 2 lemonades with 90mg Delta 8 THC and it did not do anything for me or my boyfriend. I spent $49 and I am very disappointed. We were super excited to try the drinks! But definitely not worth it.

Had to try out their delta 8 edibles! Long lines for sure, pretty expensive but great to try at least once! I went 2 days ago and they only accepted cash. (atm near by) @wake-n-bakery pls leave on ur digital menu by the window longer, thanks

Daily THC user, the food and coffee tastes great, But DONT spend money on anything infused, if you want edibles make your own (super easy) or go to a dispensary. I purchased the macros (3) Ate two of them and didnt feel anything.  $90 later i was sober, it was cool for the experience its a cute little shop, not worth spending money at. Coffee was good, had a hint of thx so it was the best item out of all 4 infused items bought. Wouldn’t recommend for thx purpose, strictly only for a small coffee shop.
got 80 mg worth of stuff, service was really good but after 2 hours we feel no effects :(
The rose lemonade is 🔥 Peanut butter cookies and a white chocolate coffee was also delish. Bring cash, they don't accept any other forms of payment. There is an ATM right next to it though.

Besides the hour wait, my first experience was pleasurable. It’s cash only, so beware of that. It seems that they run out pretty quickly, so make sure to get there early if there’s something you really want. I’ll definitely be back to try more treats.

Place is awesome! We got 2 cookies,  a lemon poppy seed muffin (WHICH WAS AMAZING) a huge rice crispy and a drink all for $75 which is a great price. All of it was infused with THC! Definitely recommend, we drove an hour and a half just to come here!

The people working here were very friendly, and the vibe of this place is super cool! My girlfriend and I ordered the pink crush kush and the cafe con leche, both with 60 mg, and a chocolate chip cookie. Everything was delicious! Although the service, ambiance, and food were excellent, we felt that the added THC did not have any affect on either of us. For $55, we anticipated to feel something. We will return again to give it another try!
Great and friendly staff worth the wait the hand crafted drinks are great and the lemon poppyseed almond muffin is bombbbb
This place is wonderful! The edibles are tasty!! And the drinks... Yes!! Staff is just as amazing as the products! Loved the vibes! Definitely see more visits in the near future.

Omg this place was so cute. The staff was super nice,  the vibe of the store was iconic, and the drinks were honestly really good!  I got a THC scone and my drink infused w/ CBD and I did feel some slight effects (I do have a THC tolerance already, so if you have a tolerance the effects might be more dulled). My best friend has 0 tolerance and got her drink & scone infused with THC and she was ZOOTED. So, tread carefully with how much you infuse if you're not a typical THC user. Awesome place to check out !!!

The service and shop was amazing. I was greeted and helped by a great staff that had a lot of energy. However, after I payed $42.00 on a double f it white chocolate latte; I was disappointed with the results as it had seemed as if I purchased an ordinary coffee. I would love to come again as I enjoyed the environment and give the benefit of the doubt I picked the wrong item.

This place is incredible. Staff is super friendly, I love that they have dairy free/vegan options, and the pistachio latte is ridiculously good. Can’t recommend enough. They only accept cash/venmo/cash app so keep that in mind.
Friendly and very helpful staff. Great treats!

Love this place! There is sometimes a line but it’s worth the wait. The staff is very friendly and knowledgeable, and can help explain everything if it’s your first time. The cheesecake pastries are BOMB.
First time there and the pastchio latte was good it must go
Everything you’d expect and more
It's busy but quite worth the wait!! Fantastic staff, service is impeccable, and the goodies are tasty & healthy.

I went here tonight with high hopes, but unfortunately was disappointed with the pricing/results. For a coffee that costed $4.25, I paid an additional $20 to add 120mg of THC. For a total of $24.00, I felt nothing. Even after waiting hours, which was really disappointing. I also tried the cinnamon coffee cake muffin which was priced at $10 with 40mg, but again felt nothing. Given I paid $40.00 for my entire order (which did taste good nonetheless), I just would have expected better end results. Maybe lower prices given the amount of THC perhaps. Wasn't impressed 😧
Visited Wednesday afternoon for the first time. Awesome staff! Super friendly and great prices!
Have been here a couple of times and their drinks are awesome! I am excited to go back and try more!

Went drove from the north west side to try out some edibles on a Sunday. The line was extremely long but it was probably because of the chai latte that had gone viral on Twitter a couple days prior. I started out in line by the Jewel and it took a little over 1.5 hours to get to the front door. Staff was super friendly and patient while I ordered since it was my first time there and I wasn’t well aquatinted with the menu. I ordered a dirty iced chai latte with 90mg of THC added. Since I weigh around 200 lbs it usually takes about 30 mg of THC or more for me to feel some type of high. I drank the whole thing within 30 minutes and after 2.5 hours I barely felt a slight buzz. Once that buzz went away I ate a whole bag of the gummy edibles. The barista said that the bags were 50mg each; the first bag had gummy bears and sour patch kids. After 1.5 hours I was zooted. I was a upset that the $10 bag of gummies worked better than my $20 dollar latte, but at last I was actually high. I had another bag of gummies I was excited about, so I ate the whole bag of lip shape gummies the next day and expected the same result as the bag from yesterday but absolutely NOTHING happened. Not even a buzz. I’m not a heavy smoker and I do not smoke everyday so I don’t understand why the edibles did not hit. I’m disappointed in the inconsistency of the product. The staff was super nice and the lobby was clean, had good music playing and was very decorative. Definitely a good vibe. The product was not worth the $50 spent.

So to Clarify they have drinks that have CBD, & Delta 8 THC, it is not the same as regular THC. Chicago is in its 1st year of the recreational cannabis program & as far as that goes it's just dispensaries where you can buy products there are no places here in the City where you're getting actual THC-A infused Teas & Coffees that are strain specific, for that experience you would have to go somewhere in Colorado, California, Oregon or Washington; where the laws are more developed to allow such a concept. If it was actually weed with how the prices are currently, those drinks would cost $25/$40.  This is an establishment what some would consider 'tease beverages', sorry to say but that's not the actual white widow strain or Ak-47 mixed in with your drink, plenty of other places do this when naming their menu items i.e Cheeba Hut.  As someone who's from Colorado where it's normal to see marijuana mixed in with food at certain coffee shops/dab lounges this was kinda a let down.  However they did have some great veggie burritos as well as their sweets & The staffs service was very welcoming & kind.

Checked this place out for the first time yesterday, and I absolutely will be back. The coffee and pastries are amazing, the staff is more amazing! Johnny and Steven took great care of my friend and I on my bday city trip. Highly recommend this place, you will NOT be disappointed!
Definitely an awesome place to start your day

Had to wait a little while outside and they were only allowing two people at a time. Service was really nice though. It was our first time coming here and the coffee was good although the drinks hit us pretty hard though. I have no idea how much THC they put but it definitely was alot as I still felt the after affects the next day. I wouldn't mind coming back back but maybe asking them to reduce how much they put. Prices are fair as I spent around $20 for my sister and I on two coffee drinks.
great service! great products! great vibes! all-around great place!
Super kind workers and great pastries!

Such a cute cafe with so many choices! I got a lavender vanilla latte w 50 mg and it had me giddy already within a couple sips and I'm a daily smoker. I nabbed a peach cheesecake bite too for a really affordable price! Staff were so informative and helpful. Definitely coming back to support this business and get more sweet treats!
Love the pepper mint mocha with THC And cuban coffee cake edible, it was a lil pricy but Well worth a visit, and the employees are friendly and vary helpful don't forget to give them a tip!!!
Edibles don’t work, friendly people, bad product.
Our first, but def not last visit!! Staff was GREAT!!! Service was GREAT!! Prices and quality were also GREAT!! We will be coming back in the near future!!
I had a latte that put me on my as. It took a couple of hours so I doubted it but boy was I wrong!! The people there are really really nice! The bar fellas were super cute and friendly.
Fantastic service, cookies are delicious and I highly recommend the passion fruit lemonade infused. Mmmm
Friendly service! The drinks and  pastries were good.

Staff was great and an overall very cute place, however the products don’t work! Spent over 100$ there on a drink and a few edibles that didn’t even do anything. Ate them all in one sitting and still nothing, very disappointed.

Came in on a Monday morning, no line no wait. Staff was super friendly, attentive, & informative. They explained the menu to us and gave us time to make our decisions. We ended up going with three THC infused baked goods (including the WAP, which we couldn’t say no to) and 2 CBD infused drinks: the price added up to about $55 which we found very reasonable. The baked goods were yummy and fresh. The CBD drinks were awesome! The taste was amazing & the cbd left us feeling very relaxed yet attentive! I would love to come back and dine in once it’s deemed safe to do so. Thanks to the staff for making our first experience a great one!

The staff is very welcoming and knowledgeable about their products. The drinks are very good but they are somewhat pricy. I greatly appreciated that they had vegan options that definitely hit, had me out like a light. The pumpkin spice latte and snoop latte was amazing!!
This place is great 🌬
Delta 8 is a scam that doesn't get you high
Waited in line for an hour. I bought two drinks and two pastries that were extremely small for $50!! Too overpriced for something that doesn’t even work. Don’t waste your time and money.

WELL WORTH THE WAIT. You may be in line for 30min on a busy weekend, but they only allow 2 guests in at a time which is understandable. It was a little intimidating as a first time visitor with how many options you have, but there’s tons to sample and the very helpful staff walk you through the options. The Lavender Vanilla latte was fabulous, with an extra “shot” of THC. The pastries are all *high* quality bakes, that I’d eat regardless of their special ingredients. Cannot wait to go back!!!

Staff is unbelievably friendly and helpful to first time shoppers. Menu items are easily customizable with whatever amount of THC you would like in your treat. Coffee selection is great too! If you aren’t a huge THC fan but love to reap the benefits of CBD - this place us got you covered. I will definitely be returning :)
This place is great , their customer service is great, the products are good & worth every penny. If you love bud & baked goods plus drinks... this is the place.
Very friendly staff! Would def recommend others to check this place out

Love this place! The people who work there are super nice and personable. The baked goods taste AMAZING and with a little added THC, they make you feel good too. I just love the vibe and concept of this place. I highly recommend people check it out.

I’ve been a “regular” for a while, but it’s getting more difficult due to long lines! Seriously, this speaks to the awesome products and more so to the overall “vibe” of Wake and Bakery. You feel it as soon as you walk through the door.
Really good food and coffee! It's a great time!

I was looking forward to coming here, but was unfortunately disappointed. I was greeted by all the very friendly and helpful staff. I got 2 thc infused White Widow coffees, with three 25mg shots each(after reading they were on the lighter side). I also purchased the Delta 8 Piggy which seemed more like a whipped cream filled brick. My girlfriend couldn't even bite through it without hurting her teeth, but I tried to keep an open mind. I took the burden of finishing it. After leaving and getting back in my car, my coffee lid breaks. Plastics lands in my cup, and coffees spills on me. I reluctantly fished it out, and I tried my coffee only to find it unsweetened. It was a cozy little shop with nice staff but I won't be returning.
great friendly staff but pretty over-hyped. the coffee wasn’t that great & the lids were cheap & broke off into my drink. 80$ for 2 coffees that didn’t even taste good.
Saw this place on tic tok and was excited to try it, the experience was fun but I spent 50 dollars on the delta 8 products and didn’t feel anything, super disappointed
Pretty awesome food they lady was so excited to me have a great fing day lol I felt high and pet my squirrel after pretty awesome day

I was taken there by the lady and her friend a couple days ago. When I first walked into the bakery/cafe it has a very cozy at home vibe to enjoy their treats and drinks! I tried their strawberry cupcake, vanilla cupcake, and a chai latte (all with THC). The treats and drink were lovely along with the experience I would just say the prices are a little taxed but other than that would recommend for anyone even first-timers.
Loved the staff! Cookies were fresh and so warm! Lemon skunk drink is so good! 😊
Best lavender latte in Chicago! And baked goods cant be beat try their triple berry

This cafe is just the cutest! Super friendly and knowledgeable staff - makes you feel so welcomed. Had the Lavender Vanilla latte with thc and it was SO GOOD! Cute cozy spot, will definitely make it a go to spot when I'm in the area!

Great experience at this café. Such an innovative idea that's really well executed. I had a PSL and it was EXACTLY the pick me up that I expected. Will be a repeat customer for sure and highly recommend people check it out!
Historic neighborhood bakery. Breakfast sandwiches and baked goods are worth a stop. Seating available for a few small groups.
This place is the jam. I highly recommend getting the Delta-8 in your coffee.

Brianna was so amazing! She patiently answered all of my questions I had about all her products and the process that goes into making them! I love the hard work and dedication that goes behind such a wonderful, inviting business. The environment is so cozy and friendly, welcoming any and all walks of life. I’ll definitely be back time and time again. 🍪

Amazing quality, very friendly, their Delta 8 THC is  exceptional, no wait in lines like dispensaries, also prices are the best compared to anywhere in Town Hands down best THC drinks and edibles i ever tried

Aweful food. Waited 45 minutes for 2 wraps.  The person working was awesome but alone.  Large crowds and to much for her to handle alone.  She was extremely sweet and kept apologizing.  Wasn't her fault but not planning on going back.

I absolutely adore this coffee shop. Thc aside...their coffee is superb and their bakeries taste super fresh. I highly recommend getting a dose in your coffee and definitely check out the cookies . Yum!!!!😍

Astounding variety of drinks on the menu, and some very creative fruit teas. The Pink Crush Kush was absolutely dynamite. Small outdoor seating area for enjoying your food and drinks, too.  Staff was awesome! Our barista was patient with our questions and fast on the drinks. Definitely going to be one of my new go-to spots.
Never disappointed! Amazing customer service and delicious food and drinks! Adding the delta 8 thc makes a hell of difference in my day! Starbucks who??? Wake-n-Bakery has all my business now!
My favorite coffee place in the area, very friendly staff and great local service! The owner is also very kind and easy to talk to. Definitely recommend! I love de Delta 8 THC!

Super friendly staff and great customer service! This spot is unlike any other coffee shop in Chicago, such a fun vibe and a great place to do some work or just hang out. The coffee is killer and the baked goods are  amazing as well. Quickly becoming one of my favorite spots in the area. Also, THC coming soon!

This place is amazing! I’ve tried many different specialty drinks and have never been disappointed. The staff is friendly and knowledgeable, so if you’ve never had a CBD or THC infused drink this is the place to try it. None of the drinks come with anything infused into them so it’s a great place to drop in for your morning coffee, then come back to for your afternoon fun! Do yourself a favor and GO HERE!
Great coffee place. My friend and I stopped and order Coñatas to go. I got a chocolate and my friend a peanut butter one. They are fun and are filled with chocolate. Great and fun pastry.

I got a cookie - $8 for 25mg THC - and let me tell you... nah let me show you (pic below). Im definitely going back to try out more of the food and coffee!  I think it would be dope if they had a secret patio, hideout, speakeasy or something!
Love  wake-N-Bake this place chai  tea latte is so good and it has other goodies to that are not THC

Kinda feel gypped, to he honest. I got 2 shots of thc (50 mg total) in a lemonade drink (16oz). Tasty drink, I didn't feel the thc at all. At $40 total for this, I wouldn't come back.  Super friendly staff nonetheless, but I've had a 10mg gummy and felt more than this. Save your money, go to a dispensary for intoxicants.
This place is a must if you are in the boystown Lakeview area. Amazing products and customer service.

Coolest new spot in Lakeview! Super welcoming, calming, and clean! Delicious lemonade and taco Tuesday with the incredible Chef Ashley! They even have space to work and free printing for us WFM people! Can’t wait to come back and check out the CBD muffins!
The passion lemonade was delicious with cbd!

I highly recommend everybody grab something from Wake n Bakery!!  I left just 30 minutes ago. Not only is the tea that I bought so delicious and refreshing, but infused with CBD. I feel energized, happy, and calm all at the same time. This is my new spot and I am sooo happy they opened!
One of the best places in Lakeview or Chicago to grab anything tea or ☕ and pretty much anything ! Great employees 👍 and owner 👍!

Totally recommend! Honestly, just as you'd imagine a recreational shop, but for all the right reasons. Cool, down to earth people. Great drink options, price is understandable, but worth the buy. CBD or THC, I ordered a drink for me and my friend 'On the house' , while I bought my visiting mother a CBD drink. Kiwi is just the way to go, for sure. Left there with every intention to return. Well-done!
Amazing coffee and baked goods, Highly recommended!
Love the place
The owner was extremely helpful and kind. Best infused cookies around! Need one as a gift and she helped me pick out the perfect treat.
Vegan Brookies 🔥 🔥

Absolutely love this place! To start off the menu is very unique and has a diverse array of drinks to choose from and non-dairy options as well. If you’re in the mood for something a bit more regular, you can get that as well! The owner, Bri is such a nice and down to earth member of the community. As a nursing school student (always looking for a spot to study)I appreciate her positive energy and customer service. She creates a cool, calm and collected atmosphere with her also friendly staff. Not to mention her business donates to the local elementary school. Please don’t snooze on this place, I highly recommend the Snoop Dreams and CBD muffins.
Very cozy atmosphere and an array of product offerings. I had a scone and a coconut-based drink: delicious!

I recently visited this new coffee shop, which replaced Rewired while visiting my old neighborhood in Chicago. Both the quality of the coffee and decor were a big improvement on the previous place.  Being lactose intolerant myself, I appreciated the plethora of non-diary options. There were plenty of options of non-coffee options such as tea and hot chocolate for my family who aren't coffee drinkers. The owner was very nice and accommodating. We didn't try any CBD products, but Wake-N-Bake offers that as well. We came to Chicago on a rather cold winter day because I had a late flight at O'hare. We also had my parent's dog with us, as it was a long trip from where they live, it was too cold to leave her outside, and our dog has been having seizures so we were hesitant to leave her at home. Unfortunately, it's hard to find inside dog-friendly places in winter. The owner was very accommodating and let us bring our dog inside with us and rearrange the chairs to sit together, which was greatly appreciated.
